rndi =: ?@(}. $ }:)@$ {/"0 1 |:


NB. Example:
NB.
NB.    (rndi;rndi;rndi) 'abcd','efgh',:'ijkl'
NB. ┌────┬────┬────┐
NB. │ebkh│ebgh│ibkh│
NB. └────┴────┴────┘
NB.
NB. ([ {/"0 1 |:@]) is a long way to say } when you need it to be a verb.
NB.
NB. This was inspired by a discussion of genetic algorithms. It seems like
NB. this would be a useful way to 'breed' multiple paren strings.
